<HEADLINE>
<P>
JOHN TOWER'S REJECTION BY THE SENATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vice President Dan Quayle's foot-stamping, emotional response to the Tower 
defeat, accusing the Democrats in the Senate of "using McCarthyite mud-slinging 
tactics" against Tower as part of a deliberate campaign to undermine the 
presidency (Part I, March 11) seems an odd route for him to take to screech at 
the 53 senators who voted against Tower's confirmation. 
</P>
<P>
Given Quayle's ultra-conservative views and his family's past affiliation with 
the John Birch Society, it would not be far-fetched to assume that Quayle would 
have stood up to be counted as one of Joe McCarthy's staunchest supporters. 
</P>
<P>
ARTHUR LEWIS 
</P>
