<HEADLINE>
<P>
UPROAR OVER TWO FLAG EXHIBITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The response of offended Muslims to the book "The Satanic Verses" is not unlike 
the response of Christians to the movie "The Last Temptation of Christ." The 
difference is in degree: violence or peaceful demonstration. But the basic 
issue of each is the violation of conscience and the fear of misinterpretation 
of truth in their religion. 
</P>
<P>
Now, consciences are being violated as the American flag is walked on in the 
name of art. The consciences of citizens hurt as the symbol of unity is defiled 
for the artist's individual freedom. 
</P>
<P>
Is there no end to the discounting of others' beliefs? To be effective, freedom 
always has to have limits (such as obedience to the law); but a far greater 
limit is that of not doing anything that would hurt my brother. 
</P>
<P>
MARY SMITH 
</P>
<P>
Canyon Country 
</P>
</TEXT>
