<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man whom police have dubbed the "Walk-to-the-Back" bandit, robbed a beauty 
supply store Friday for an undisclosed amount of cash, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The robbery is believed to be one in a series of more than 30 similar holdups 
that began in December, San Diego police spokesman Bill Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
The bandit walked into Lubey Beauty and Barber Supply in the 3600 block of 
Midway Drive just after 4 p.m., showed a handgun and ordered a female clerk to 
walk to the back of the store, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
He rifled the cash register and fled, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
He has robbed small businesses in East San Diego, La Mesa and El Cajon, usually 
selecting one where a female employee is working alone, Robinson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
