<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL TRACK; 
</P>
<P>
BOWLING LEAPS TO FORE IN UPSET OF KENNEDY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eddie Bowling of Canoga Park High made a name for himself last season in the 
high jump, winning the City Section championship. And in the early stages of 
the '89 season, he has developed into a standout in the long jump and triple 
jump as well. 
</P>
<P>
He won all three events in a Northwest Valley Conference track meet against 
Kennedy on Friday, as the Hunters upset the Golden Cougars, 66-59, at Canoga 
Park. 
</P>
<P>
Bowling, a senior, also anchored the victorious mile relay (3 minutes, 35.2 
seconds) as Canoga Park (2-1, 2-1 in league meets) won nine of 15 events, 
including both relays. 
</P>
<P>
Bowling, who leaped 6 feet, 4 inches in the high jump, 21-5 in the long jump 
and 43-10 in the triple jump, had plenty of help from his teammates, 
particularly Robin Kim. 
</P>
<P>
Kim won the 100 in 10.8 seconds, the 200 in 22.4, anchored Canoga Park's 
victorious 400 relay (44.2) and ran the third leg on the mile relay. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy (2-1) was paced by George Duran, who won the 1,600 (4:49.0) and 3,200 
(10:25.6). 
</P>
<P>
In other boys' meets: 
</P>
<P>
Birmingham 96, Poly 31 -- After missing last week's meet because of 
disciplinary reasons, the Braves' Rodney Burt returned with a vengeance in the 
Valley Pac-8 Conference meet at Birmingham. 
</P>
<P>
Burt won the 100 in 11.1, the 200 in 22.7, the 400 in 49.7 and anchored the 
victorious 400 relay (44.5) as Birmingham (3-0) remained undefeated. 
</P>
<P>
Taft 95, Granada Hills 32 -- Cornell Hill won two events for Taft in the 
Northwest Valley Conference meet at home. Hill won the high jump at 6-0 and the 
long jump at 21-1 as the Toreadors (2-1) won all five field events. Teammate 
Rejesh Chauhan won the pole vault at 13-0. 
</P>
<P>
San Fernando 72, Chatsworth 51 -- Ibed Aguirre and Keary Johns each won two 
events for the Tigers (2-1) in the Northwest Valley Conference meet at 
Chatsworth. 
</P>
<P>
Aguirre won the mile (4:38.6) and two mile (10:19.0), and Johns won the 
120-yard high hurdles (15.5) and the 330-yard intermediate hurdles (43.4). 
</P>
<P>
Cornelius Edwards won the 440 (51.9) and triple jump (43-1 1/2) for Chatsworth 
(1-2). 
</P>
<P>
Monroe 82, Sylmar 33 -- Derril White won the 100 (11.3) and long jump (20-5 
1/2) for Monroe (3-0) in a Valley Pac-8 Conference meet at home. 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 76, Canoga Park 29 -- Natasha Como won the 100 (13.1) and 200 (28.0) 
meters for Kennedy in the Northwest Valley Conference meet at Canoga Park. 
</P>
<P>
The victory improved Kennedy's record to 3-0. The Golden Cougars have a 99-5 
dual-meet record since the girls' team was formed in 1976. 
</P>
<P>
Birmingham 76 1/2, Poly 32 1/2 -- Freshman Heather Ballard won four events for 
Birmingham in the Valley Pac-8 Conference meet at home. 
</P>
<P>
Ballard ran 2:37.9 in the 800 and 52.7 in the 300 low hurdles, leaped 4-8 in 
the high jump and put the shot, 28-11. 
</P>
<P>
Granada Hills 58, Taft 51 -- Toreador sophomore Jane Kim won four events, but 
Granada Hills prevailed in the Northwest Valley Conference meet at Taft. 
</P>
<P>
Kim won the 220-yard dash (27.6), the 100-meter low hurdles (16.3), the 300 
hurdles (49.5) and the long jump (15-6). 
</P>
