<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
INCONSISTENT NORTHRIDGE SWEPT IN VOLLEYBALL MATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal State Northridge men's volleyball team has been struggling to find the 
winning combination. 
</P>
<P>
Friday night at the CSUN gym it was more of the same. The Matadors played well, 
but not well enough, and were swept by Long Beach State, 15-11, 15-8, 17-15, in 
a Western Intercollegiate Volleyball Assn. match. 
</P>
<P>
Fifth-ranked Long Beach State (16-5, 7-4 in conference play) sailed through the 
first game, helped by CSUN's eight service faults. 
</P>
<P>
The 49ers also controlled the second game before CSUN awoke to make a match of 
it in the final game. 
</P>
<P>
Setter Tom Ribarich paced the Matadors (7-15, 2-11) with 47 assists and 15 
digs. Outside hitter Bob Samuelson added 22 kills and three assists and Neil 
Coffman had 17 kills. PAUL OLSON 
</P>
