<HEADLINE>
<P>
OPERA, WITH NO QUOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was at the March 4 performance of "Tancredi" by the Music Center Opera 
Company and I found the handling of Chris Merritt's laryngitis ingenious. I 
enjoyed seeing him perform and lip-sync the words, and I found the generosity 
of Merritt and the rest of the cast toward Stephen Gould (who did the actual 
singing) refreshing. 
</P>
<P>
If that makes me an "opera" lover rather than an opera (no quotes) lover, so be 
it. 
</P>
<P>
William Stockman (Letters, March 11) says we got what we deserved. He thinks 
someone else deserves his seat. I think he does not deserve our splendid Music 
Center Opera Company. 
</P>
<P>
MARY W. BAILEY 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
