<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND CHECKLIST FOR DIGGERS AND PLANTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen: 
</P>
<P>
Now is a good time to look for dwarf citrus at nurseries. Consider using dwarf 
citrus in large containers for a decorative touch and a tasty harvest of 
full-sized fruit. 
</P>
<P>
Spring is the time to start a regular fertilizing program for all areas of the 
garden. 
</P>
<P>
This is a good time to plant star jasmine for fragrant blooms at the base of a 
fence or wall. 
</P>
<P>
Sow vegetables such as lettuce, radishes, corn and carrots in successive 
plantings to lengthen the harvest time. 
</P>
<P>
Rake up and dispose of old camellia blooms and leaves, to prevent the spread of 
petal blight. 
</P>
<P>
Watch for aphids that attack new rose growth. 
</P>
