<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRAZIL CHARGES 4 IN NEW YEAR'S EVE SHIP CAPSIZING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police charged four people Thursday in the capsizing of a Brazilian tourist 
ship that killed 55 party-goers who planned to spend New Year's Eve watching 
the fireworks on Copacabana Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The charges of putting lives at risk on public transport were lodged against 
two of the ship's owners, the owner of the travel agency that arranged the trip 
and the ship's mechanic. They carry a maximum sentence of 24 years in prison 
upon conviction. 
</P>
<P>
A total of 125 people testified at an inquiry which concluded that the ship had 
been poorly maintained and was overloaded as it set out just before midnight 
last New Year's Eve. 
</P>
