<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHALLENGE TO ABORTION FUNDING LAW DISMISSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DETROIT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A judge on Friday dismissed a teen-age gang-rape victim's challenge to 
Michigan's voter-approved law cutting off state-funded abortions for poor 
women. 
</P>
<P>
Wayne County Circuit Judge John H. Hausner ruled the law bars an abortion for 
the girl, since her life is not endangered by the pregnancy. He said the law 
does not violate Michigan's Constitution. 
</P>
<P>
The American Civil Liberties Union brought the suit on behalf of the girl, and 
its lawyers promised to appeal. The girl, now about nine weeks pregnant, has 
been offered money for a private abortion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
