<HEADLINE>
<P>
ZIEGLER PROVIDES A GOOD EXAMPLE IN PROBERT CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NHL president John Ziegler does not rule his sport with the authority of the 
other three major sports commissioners, but at times his decisions are 
noteworthy. 
</P>
<P>
The recent expulsion of Detroit Red Wing all-star Bob Probert is a good 
example. Probert used drugs, was caught and removed from the game. Unlike other 
sports that try to work with the athletes, the NHL respects the players and 
treats them as normal people. Namely, abuse drugs and you'll be excused from 
your livelihood. 
</P>
<P>
No slaps on the wrist for three-time offenders as in the NBA and major league 
baseball. 
</P>
<P>
ANDREW JAMNER 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
