<HEADLINE>
<P>
ART OF UNDERSTATEMENT LEAVES HIM WONDERING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
My ribs still ache from laughing at the Morning Briefing column (March 6) 
discussing the $1.3-million prize of this summer's Tour de France. "Not bad for 
pedaling a bike across a couple of hills" was the last line. 
</P>
<P>
By that standard: Joe Montana and Jerry Rice played "catch" in the Super Bowl; 
Kirk Gibson's game-winning shot in the World Series was "batting practice at 
the local high school," and the L.A. Marathon was a "stroll to the local 
tanning salon." 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT MEEKER 
</P>
<P>
Ojai 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031889-0077 </DOCNO>
