</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The owners of the Dallas Sidekicks must post $260,000 by Monday to keep the 
Major Indoor Soccer League team from being taken over by its creditors, a 
bankruptcy judge ordered. 
</P>
<P>
The Sidekicks filed for bankruptcy last month after learning that the Dallas 
Mavericks, the former owners, planned to foreclose on a $330,000 note. 
</P>
<P>
The Sidekicks have until June 20 to file a reorganization plan, provided they 
meet Monday's deadline. 
</P>
