<HEADLINE>
<P>
OXNARD SANTA CLARA WINS DIVISION IV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oxnard Santa Clara High School's Bubba Burrage connected on 11 of 14 field goal 
attempts and scored 22 points to lead the Saints to a 61-48 victory over Santa 
Rosa Cardinal Newman Friday night at Ventura College to win the State Division 
IV boys' basketball title. 
</P>
<P>
Cardinal Newman (31-4) scored the first six points of the game, but Santa Clara 
came back to take a 15-12 first-quarter lead and thenhold the Cardinals without 
a field goal in the second quarter while opening a 28-20 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
Junior Shon Tarver and John McGill added 15 and 14 points, respectively, for 
Santa Clara. Mike Hostetter was the leading scorer for Cardinal Newman with 14. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Clara finished the season 27-3, but that included two forfeit losses. Its 
only loss on the court was to Edison of Huntington Beach, 39-38. 
</P>
