</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oil Prices Soar: Oil futures prices rocketed past the $20-a-barrel mark as the 
momentum that began building on Monday swept the market higher for the fifth 
consecutive day. On the New York Mercantile Exchange, the April contract for 
West Texas Intermediate crude, the benchmark grade of U.S. oil, leaped 49 cents 
to a 19-month high of $20.33 a barrel in moderate trading. It was the highest 
level since Aug. 14, 1987, when crude prices were $20.57 a barrel, and capped a 
weeklong rally during which prices rose $1.83 a barrel from last Friday's close 
of $18.50. 
</P>
