<P>
Swissair to Start L.A. Service: Swissair announced that it will begin scheduled 
flights between Los Angeles and Switzerland on Nov. 1, starting with nonstops 
to Zurich on Mondays, Wednesdays and Saturdays. Daily service is envisioned by 
1991. Meanwhile, Swissair and Delta Air Lines announced a "partnership" between 
the two airlines and said they would coordinate flight schedules to offer 
passengers fast connections on routes to and from North America. They also plan 
to share reservation systems and airport facilities and to advertise their 
services jointly. But "we are not looking for a merger of our companies," 
Swissair's Chairman Armin Baltensweiler said. 
