<TEXT>
<P>
Gang members lobbed a Molotov cocktail into a South Los Angeles house early 
Friday, injuring three people, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
A woman in her 50s and a young man and woman escaped with minor smoke 
inhalation in the attack, which occurred about 1 a.m. when a carload of 
suspected gang members threw the device through the window of a house in the 
5400 block of 2nd Avenue, police and fire officials said. 
</P>
