<P>
 LESBIAN LOVER WINS ROUND ON CUSTODY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman will be allowed to seek joint custody of her former female lover's 
daughter, who was born during their lesbian relationship, a Los Angeles 
Superior Court judge has ruled. 
</P>
<P>
"It's exciting that a person who is not a natural biological parent can proceed 
in a same-sex relationship case," said attorney Gloria Allred, who is 
representing the mother's former lover, Terri Sabol. 
</P>
<P>
After a closed session with attorneys for Sabol and the mother, who has not 
been identified, Superior Court Commissioner James Endman allowed the custody 
case to proceed. 
</P>
<P>
Endman ruled that if a nonparent can be ordered to pay child support, then a 
nonparent should be allowed to seek custody of a child. 
</P>
