<P>
WOODBRIDGE SOFTBALL TOURNAMENT STARTS TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Defending Southern Section 4-A champion Gahr High School will be one of 40 
teams (24 varsity and 16 junior varsity) participating in the seventh 
Woodbridge Easter softball tournament beginning at 9 a.m. today at Harvard Park 
in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Gahr, the tournament's defending champion, is led by All-Southern Section 
pitcher DeDe Weiman. 
</P>
<P>
Weiman will set the standard for up-and-coming county pitchers competing in the 
tournament. They include Lisa Wehren, who was part of Woodbridge's 2-A 
championship team last season; Paige Lauby of El Toro, who is 4-0 this season 
and was named the most valuable player of the Corona tournament; Marta Bickert, 
who had an 0.89 earned-run average for Trabuco Hills last season, and Margo 
Melendrez of Laguna Hills, an All-Southern Section 2-A selection last season. 
</P>
<P>
Pool play begins today. Based on their showing in pool play, teams compete in 
the winners', consolation or losers' bracket under a double-elimination format. 
Games resume Monday through Wednesday and the championship game will be 
Wednesday at 5 p.m. 
</P>
